Early Years Teacher Assistant (Aged 3 – 5) for Academic Year 2023/24Shrewsbury International School BangkokJob Highlights
International environment
Early Years Teacher Assistant
Career advancementTo direct apply for Early Years Teacher Assistant (Aged 3 – 5) for Academic Year 2023/24, applicants must complete the English language version of the application form.

Key Responsibilities:


The Early Years Teacher Assistant reports directly to Assistant Principal (Pre-Prep) and Assistant Principal (Pre-Prep) is responsible as part of a team for the effective operation of the Junior School. In particular, the Early Years Teacher Assistant will


be responsible to the Assistant Principals (Junior);
be line managed by the Year Team Leader with day to day direction from the Class Teacher;
work closely with the Class Teacher to provide stimulating learning opportunities for the children;
work closely with the Class Teacher to provide for student’s learning, social and personal needs;
work with other professionals in meeting the needs of students; 
attend staff meetings and training and development sessions as required.
other ad hoc duties as requested.
Tasks:


The Early Years Teacher Assistant’s role is a class based position. The Early Years Teacher Assistant will


support the school’s Philosophy and Objectives;
take an active part in all class and year group activities;
work with groups and individuals on learning tasks;
observe and interact with children during Active Learning and comment on their progress;
assist in the assessment of students and suggest provision linked to children’s interests;
prepare materials and resources for indoor and outdoor learning opportunities;
assist  in  the  setting  up  and  maintaining  of  an  efficient  and  well-ordered learning environment;
take an active role in classroom administration;
assist in, ‘Home Communication’;
participate in training and development activities;
undertake lunchtime and after school duties in accordance with the duty roster;
participate in, “You-Time”  Activities;
follow the Early Years positive behaviour management strategies;
provide individual support for students.
Professional Expectations:


The Early Years Teacher Assistant should have the following qualities


possess at least bachelor degree;
experience of working in an Early Years setting or with Early Years aged children (3-5 years);
understanding of the age related expectations for children in the Early Years;
open to children learning through play;
ability to see learning opportunities in children’s play and have the skills to develop this;
have excellent communication and interpersonal skills;
have an understanding of teaching and learning strategies;
be professional in approach and set good examples;
be conscientious, efficient and organised;
give high regard to Health and Safety;
actively seek to improve their practice and participate in Training and Development;
have high regard to creating a high quality learning environment;
maintain the confidentiality of information.
Requirements:

Satisfactory Thai Police Criminal Record check 
Confirmation of identity
Satisfactory references
Verification of qualifications and work experience
Certificate or record of complete course of covid of an approved vaccine.
How to Apply:
Applications will only be accepted on the official Shrewsbury International School Bangkok Application Form, which is available on the school website “Job Vacancies” page. The application is preferably in English. Thai version is an option for the candidate who is keen to apply but not proficient in English.undefined

Asset Manager (Thailand)/Asset ManagerConstant EnergyJob Highlights
Fluent in English in both Writing and Speaking
Electrical Eng with exp in renewable esp. solar
Analytical skillsDescription

The Asset Manager is responsible for the reporting and budgeted performance of the assigned assets (solar PV rooftop or Utility-scale PV or Energy Storage System), smooth transition from Project Management (EPC stage) to Asset Management team (starting prior to Commercial Operation Date), keeping permitting / licenses up to date as per local regulation. The key responsibilities include:

Ensure optimum performance of the assets to meet/exceed production forecasts;
Monitor the capital expenditures and ensure they remain within budget (pro-rated to income)
Monitor daily the asset performance through Asset Management Software;
Report daily the asset performance;
Conduct data analysis and troubleshoot potential or existing issues;
Advise on any potential improvements of the assets;
Inspect the assets monthly and issue associated reporting (internal and external when applicable);
Issue quarterly reporting (internal and external when applicable),
Attend periodic follow-up meetings, internal and with external parties;
Understand the O&M Agreements in full, and ensure their enforcement when applicable;
Understand the insurance policies in full, and process/follow-up claims when applicable;
Ensure timely renewal and renegotiation of O&M Agreements and insurance policies;
Ensure timely renewal of asset operating licenses and permits;
Supervise the O&M partners and control their preventive/corrective maintenance tasks;
Ensure timely issuance and correctness of monthly power invoices;
Ensure compliant filing through could-based Box.com;
Assist the M&A team in performing technical due diligence in view of acquisition (projects in Asia)
Support at times the Project Management and Development team on Asset Management matters
Support the Finance team on required information required for operating assets by lenders and investors
Job Requirements

No need for much experience as long as they can prove good skills in;
Proficiency in Contractual Management is required
Understanding and Communicating in English (mainly you'll be using English with your reporting manager)
Have analytical skills (work with numbers)
Good at following up and reporting skills
Must have experience in solar power plant/ Corporate/PPA can be learned on the job
Having Electrical background (Bachelor in Engineering or related field)
Not a senior positionundefined
